Quote: NORTH AUCKLAND FARMERS CO-OPERATIVE LIMITED. ... Looking at the paid up capital, viz., GBP120,376, and taking a glance at the reserve for income tax (GBP9468) the astounding position is discovered that the preference shareholders are practically receiving fifteen per cent., and for that reason the ordinaries are only able to get a seven per cent. dividend, and they, too, are "slathered up" for eight per cent. of taxation.
